ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convolution_theorem" title=3D"Convolution theore=
m">Convolution theorem</a> for a derivation of that property of convolution=
. Conversely, convolution can be derived as the inverse Fourier transform o=
f the pointwise product of two Fourier transforms.
