</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/b76f8c931c10d6caf9d2a2ba919e39bc5ce90717" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.005ex; width:20.877ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \|=
{f}*g\|_{p}\leq \|f\|_{1}\|g\|_{p}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>In the particular case <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>p</i> =3D 1</span>, th=
is shows that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>L</i><sup>1</sup></span> is a <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banach_algebra" title=3D"Banach algebr=
a">Banach algebra</a> under the convolution (and equality of the two sides =
holds if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">f</span>=
 and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">g</span> are=
 non-negative almost everywhere).
</p><p>More generally, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Young%27s_c=
onvolution_inequality" title=3D"Young's convolution inequality">Young's ine=
quality</a> implies that the convolution is a continuous bilinear map betwe=
en suitable <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>L</i><sup><i>p</i></sup></span> spac=
es. Specifically, if <span class=3D"texhtml"> 1 =E2=89=A4 <i>p</i>, <i>q</i=
>, <i>r</i> =E2=89=A4 =E2=88=9E</span> satisfy:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
