<p>The optimal value of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>B</i><sub><i>p</i>,<i>q<=
/i></sub></span> was discovered in 1975<sup id=3D"cite_ref-24" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convolution#cite_note-24">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup> and independently in 1976,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-25" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convolution#cite_note-25"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brascamp%E2%80%93Li=
eb_inequality" title=3D"Brascamp=E2=80=93Lieb inequality">Brascamp=E2=80=93=
Lieb inequality</a>.
</p><p>A stronger estimate is true provided <span class=3D"texhtml"> 1 &lt;=
 <i>p</i>, <i>q</i>, <i>r</i> &lt; =E2=88=9E</span>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
