=88=97 <i>=CF=84</i><sub><i>x</i></sub> <i>=CE=B4</i>. So translation invar=
iance of the convolution of Schwartz functions is a consequence of the asso=
ciativity of convolution.
</p><p>Furthermore, under certain conditions, convolution is the most gener=
al translation invariant operation. Informally speaking, the following hold=
s
</p>
<dl><dd>Suppose that <i>S</i> is a bounded <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Linear_operator" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Linear operator">l=
