r distribution) <i>g</i><sub><i>S</i></sub>; that is <i>Sf</i> =3D <i>g</i>=
<sub><i>S</i></sub> =E2=88=97 <i>f</i>.</dd></dl>
<p>Thus some translation invariant operations can be represented as convolu=
tion. Convolutions play an important role in the study of <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-invariant_system" title=3D"Time-invariant syst=
em">time-invariant systems</a>, and especially <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/LTI_system_theory" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"LTI system t=
heory">LTI system theory</a>. The representing function <i>g</i><sub><i>S</=
i></sub> is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Impulse_response" =
title=3D"Impulse response">impulse response</a> of the transformation <i>S<=
/i>.
</p><p>A more precise version of the theorem quoted above requires specifyi=
ng the class of functions on which the convolution is defined, and also req=
uires assuming in addition that <i>S</i> must be a <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Continuous_linear_operator" title=3D"Continuous linear ope=
rator">continuous linear operator</a> with respect to the appropriate <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topology" title=3D"Topology">topology</=
a>. It is known, for instance, that every continuous translation invariant =
continuous linear operator on <i>L</i><sup>1</sup> is the convolution with =
a finite <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borel_measure" title=3D"B=
orel measure">Borel measure</a>. More generally, every continuous translati=
on invariant continuous linear operator on <i>L</i><sup><i>p</i></sup> for =
1 =E2=89=A4 <i>p</i> &lt; =E2=88=9E is the convolution with a <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distribution_(mathematics)#Tempered_distributio=
ns_and_Fourier_transform" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Distribution (math=
ematics)">tempered distribution</a> whose <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Fourier_transform" title=3D"Fourier transform">Fourier transform</a=
> is bounded. To wit, they are all given by bounded <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Fourier_multiplier" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Fourie=
r multiplier">Fourier multipliers</a>.
</p>
